  <section class="section home-a-story-section">
    <div class="w-layout-blockcontainer main-container w-container">
      <div class="w-layout-grid story-halves">
        <div class="story-image-wrap">
          <video
            src="/video/audiologist.mp4"
            autoplay
            muted
            loop
            playsinline
            class="image-cover"
            style="width: 100%; height: auto;"></video>
        </div>
        <div class="headline-story">
          <div class="heading-story">
            <h2 class="no-margins">
              Assistive Listening Technologies are essential tools for improving
              speech clarity in spaces where acoustics or background noise make
              communication difficult.
            </h2>
            <div class="spacer-sm"></div>
            <div class="section-divider home-c-numbers"></div>

            <h5>
              In spaces like auditoriums, classrooms, houses of worship, or
              public venues, factors such as background noise, reverberation,
              and speaker-to-listener distance can make speech difficult to
              follow — even for individuals using hearing aids or cochlear
              implants.
            </h5>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section home-a-story-section">
    <div class="w-layout-blockcontainer main-container w-container">
      <div class="w-layout-grid story-halves">
        <div class="headline-story">
          <div class="heading-story">
            <div class="spacer-sm"></div>
            <div class="section-divider home-c-numbers"></div>

            <h2 class="no-margins">
              Assistive Listening Technologies help to address this problem by
              delivering sound directly to the listener, cutting through noise
              and reverberation to enhance intelligibility.
            </h2>
            <div class="spacer-sm"></div>
            <div class="section-divider home-c-numbers"></div>

            <h5>
              For organisations, installing an effective ALS isn’t just good
              practice — it’s a key part of meeting accessibility requirements
              and creating environments that are inclusive.
            </h5>

            <h5>
              A wide range of assistive listening technologies are available
              today, and navigating the options can often feel overwhelming. At
              IAHA, our goal is to make these systems easier to understand and
              to provide clear, practical guidance on choosing the right
              solution for your needs. The most commonly used assistive
              listening technologies include:
            </h5>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="story-image-wrap">
